						<summary>

						<p>Back of the Hanumān image in a shrine at Yallāpur (old site near Hombaḷ).</p>						

						<p>12th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This badly damaged inscription in characters of about 12th century A.D., contains an elaborate description of a fight in which Habbaṇa-daṇḍanātha died. Seems to record some gift made in this connection by Purushōttama-daṇḍanātha on the representation of the <hi rend="italic">prabhu-gāvuṇḍas</hi> of the four villages and the <hi rend="italic">mahājanas</hi> of Poṁboḷal, to the Brahmajinalaya. There is a referenceto Kalachuri Bijjala-dēva.</p>						

						</summary>
